        {
          q: 'What happens if I lose my keypair?',
          a: 'The same thing that happens if you lose your SSH key today: you generate a new keypair and your collaborators issue you a new pairing code. There is no central account to "recover" because there is no central account. The old key is dead; the new one is paired fresh. Your local repository is untouched — you can still read everything on your machine — you just have to re-establish trust with your peers, which takes about thirty seconds per peer.',
